    • Constructor Detail

      • TransactionId

        public TransactionId(AccountId accountId)
        Generates a new transaction ID for the given `accountId`.

        Note that transaction IDs are made up of the current time and the account that is primarily signing the transaction. This account will also be the account that is charged for any transaction fees.

      • TransactionId

        public TransactionId(AccountId accountId,
                     Instant transactionValidStart)
        Generate a transaction ID with a given account ID and valid start time. Nota bene: executing transactions with the same ID (account ID & account start time) will throw HederaException with code DUPLICATE_TRANSACTION.

        Use the other constructor to get an ID with a known-valid transactionValidStart.

        Parameters:
        accountId -
        transactionValidStart - the time by which the transaction takes effect; must be in the past by the time it is submitted to the network.
